def: Having twenty-four leaves to a sheet; as, a twenty-fourmo form,book, leaf, size, etc.-- n.
A collection of serous fluid in the cavity of the abdomen;dropsy of the peritoneum. Dunglison.
Consisting chiefly of aloes; of the nature of aloes.
A retiring of the sea, occasioning a change of high-water mark,whereby land is gained.
A boat or raft used in the East Indies in the landing ofpassengers and goods.
A division of Tunicata including the common attached ascidians,both simple and compound. Called also Tethioidea.
